# Laravel Production Deployment Roadmap

## Phase 1 — Development Best Practices

### 1. Use Feature Branches

```bash
git checkout -b feature/new-feature
```

Purpose:

* Safe development
* Protect stable branch
* Easier rollback

---

### 2. Never Develop Directly on Live Server

Correct Flow:

```text
Local/Staging → Testing → Production
```

---

### 3. Backup `.env`

```bash
cp .env .env.backup
```

Add backup to `.gitignore`

```bash
echo ".env.backup" >> .gitignore
```

---

### 4. Run Tests Before Deployment

```bash
php artisan test
```

Stop on first failure:

```bash
php artisan test --stop-on-failure
```

---

# Phase 2 — Docker Setup

## Why Docker?

Benefits:

* Same environment everywhere
* Easy onboarding
* Isolation
* Easier scaling
* Better deployment

---

## Required Files

```text
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
.dockerignore
```

---

## Basic Dockerfile

```dockerfile
FROM php:8.5-fpm

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
    git \
    unzip \
    curl \
    libzip-dev \
    libpng-dev \
    libonig-dev \
    libxml2-dev

RUN docker-php-ext-install \
    pdo \
    pdo_mysql \
    mbstring \
    zip \
    exif \
    pcntl

COPY --from=composer:latest /usr/bin/composer /usr/bin/composer

WORKDIR /var/www

EXPOSE 9000
```

---

## Start Containers

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

